{
  "texts": [
    "Rather than use an MLP to reconstruct the semantic information from the GCN embeddings, the authors chose to use a conditional variational autoencoder [141].",
    "Doing so enables the model to generate semantic information for sketches of unseen classes, aiding the zero-shot component of the model.",
    "Discussion and conclusionIn this section, we draw upon the views of Battaglia et al. [41], and discuss how the popular Transformer [40] can be viewed through the lens of GNNs.",
    "We then discuss how its dependence on consistent structure may pose challenges should image generation techniques be applied to create new training data for image captioning.",
    "The section concludes with a final summary of the paper and an overview of the challenges and future research directions that lie ahead for graph-based 2D image understanding."
  ]
}